          304.7556675062972,
          441.9677734375
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "1. Localized Patches Improve Y/N Answering Across nearly all models, we observe consistently negative PCRI values, indicating that the models perform better when using localized patches rather than full-image input. This suggests that full-image representations introduce unnecessary context, leading to increased ambiguity in binary classification tasks.",
      "heading_level": null,
      "page_id": 13,
      "polygon": [
        [
          303.8203125,
          566.8317008014247
        ],
        [
          526.9420654911838,
          566.8317008014247
        ],
        [
          526.9420654911838,
          670.3009795191451
        ],
        [
          303.8203125,
          670.3009795191451
        ]
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "2. Patch Size Influences Performance Gains When comparing 2 \\times 2 and 3 \\times 3 patches, the latter consistently yields lower PCRI values, meaning greater patch granularity improves performance. This supports the hypothesis that more focused image regions help models resolve Y/N questions by minimizing distractions.",
      "heading_level": null,
